archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.name: Security Baseline Control Service - Scoping process
archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.documentation:
This view shows how the ISF SOGP Categories / areas are assessed, prioritized, communicated and agreed with relevant stakeholders in a way where the organization has better visibility on how organization gets security in control.
Within this process, following goals are met:
- what are the various ISF Categories, Areas and Topics which are defining the baseline - who is responsible for making sure ISF SOGP Topics are realized - how do we show how the realization of SOGP topics reflects to various frameworks and standards - how do we sign off the responsibility - how do we monitor the control implementation status
